<font color="#FF0000">TENNEESSEE LAND THAT I LOVE</font><br>
<tt>Tue Oct  7 10:59:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I 've never been to Tenneeessee,<br>
Saw a picture of that place once I think it was on the cover of National Geographic, June 1967 issue. <br><br>
Real nice folks they place their old couches and recliner chairs all along the roadway for their neighbors to be able to just stop and rest a spell. <br><br>
But, I guess they all worship Ford Fairlanes because they all had them up on blocks. <br>
Real animal lovers 12-13 cats to a home, 6-7 dogs and the dogs and cats all looked alike. <br>
Invitation in the magazine invited everyone to visit them, instead of champagne and caviar they served you an RC cola and a Moon pie.<br>

